{
  "texts": [
    "It follows that if A is a CV-BAO, then A u = A p is a rich frame.For part 4, that π(p) ∈ P p is immediate from Definition 5.14.5-6, so M p is based on A p, and P p ⊆ P u, so M p is based on A u as well.For part 5, φ Mp = ↓ θ(φ) can be rewritten as: for all x ∈ S, M p, x ⊩ φ iff x ⊑ θ(φ).",
    "The proof is by induction on φ.",
    "The atomic case is by definition of M p, and the ∧ case is routine.",
    "For the ¬ case, θ(¬φ) = -θ(φ), so we show that M p, x ⊩ ¬φ iff x ⊑ -θ(φ).",
    "Now x ⊑ -θ(φ) iff for all x ′ ⊑ x (so x ′ ̸ = ⊥), x ′ ̸ ⊑ θ(φ)."
  ]
}